From: m8l8th814n-eng <m8l8th814n-eng@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: qcom: sm7150-xiaomi-sweet: enable IR blaster

Redmi Note 10 Pro has a consumer-IR transmitter LED wired to QUPv3 SE8 SPI
(spi@a88000, mainline label spi8), matching downstream sweet-sdmmagpie.dtsi
(&qupv3_se8_spi / irled@0). uart8 (same SE8) is already disabled on sweet, so
the bus is free. Enable spi8 and add the ir-spi node -> /dev/lirc0 (ir-ctl).

NOTE: the mainline ir-spi driver matches compatible "ir-spi-led", NOT "ir-spi".
---
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm7150-xiaomi-sweet.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm7150-xiaomi-sweet.dts
@@ -276,6 +276,16 @@
 	};
 };
 
+&spi8 {
+	status = "okay";
+
+	irled@0 {
+		compatible = "ir-spi-led";
+		reg = <0>;
+		spi-max-frequency = <19200000>;
+	};
+};
+
 &uart8 {
 	status = "disabled";
 };
